cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the relationship between artificial intelligence, perception, cognition, computing, and mathematics, with a focus on information compression. Given this, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses visual recognition and adaptation, which suggests a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision), and the learning of lexical and grammatical structures in language, which suggests a connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
